name: Chann Fitness
bio:
My name is Chantelle. I am a personal trainer and the owner of Chann Fitness Personal Training. 

My vision as a personal trainer and social media influencer is to promote self love, confidence and happiness. Obviously I want to help people reach their physical goals of losing weight and toning their bodies, but to me, it's so much more than that. I want people to train with me and follow me programs because it makes them feel good. I want them to feel good about themselves and how hard they've worked during a training session! Most importantly, I want them to do it for themselves. There are so many negative body image influences out there and I hear so many say things like "I wish I could look like her/him". I want to show people that if you love yourself for who you are, and live a healthy, active lifestyle for YOU, you're going to feel good, be happy and you're more likely to stick to it and reach your goals! 

My goal is to make a difference. To the way people look and also the way they view themselves.

name: Jeremy Sry
bio:
I am a TEAM Bodybuilding.com Athlete, a NASM Certified Personal Trainer, a graduate from the University of California, Irvine, and an online coach. I started my fitness journey during my freshmen year of undergrad. I had an image of what I wanted to look like and an idea what to do in order to get there. To my dismay, my freshmen year did not end as I planned. I was no where near what I envisioned for my physique and I was actually pretty close to academic probation. It took me two years to effectively and efficiently restructure my priorities, my routines, and most importantly my lifestyle. By my senior year as an undergrad I can proudly tell you, I achieved a 4.0 all year long AND acquired the physique I present to you today! 

I spent most of my undergrad years struggling with my lifestyle. I can tell you at times, I felt lost and hopeless. I would never wish for anyone on their fitness journey to feel this way. My mission now is to educate and empower anyone on the pursuit of their best self. Everyone starts somewhere, but not everyone finishes what they started. If you are ready to take control of your health, I am here to help! 

"Give a man a fish, feed him for a day. Teach a man how to fish, feed him for a lifetime." 

Educate and Empower 

- Jeremy Sry

name: Dott. Filippo Scarpelli
bio:
Mi chiamo Filippo Scarpelli e sono nato a Torino. Fin da molto giovane sono rimasto affascinato dal mondo del fitness e del bodybuilding. Dopo aver praticato numerose arti marziali, che mi hanno insegnato l’importanza del sacrificio e di un allenamento costante e organizzato, mi sono avvicinato alla palestra dove trascorrevo la maggior parte del mio tempo libero. 

Gratificato dai risultati ottenuti sul mio fisico, dopo il diploma ho deciso quindi di trasformare questa passione in una professione, iscrivendomi alla Scuola universitaria inter facoltà in scienze motorie (s.u.i.s.m) dove mi sono laureato a pieni voti. Negli anni di studio universitario ho dedicato molte energie ad arricchire il mio bagaglio di conoscenze, conseguendo il brevetto di istruttore di nuoto e frequentando il corso di personal training tenuto da Luciano Gemello. 

Alla formazione rivolta alla preparazione atletica ho voluto successivamente affiancare una competenza completa nella cura del benessere fisico, dal quale ritengo discenda anche un buon equilibrio psicologico. Per questa ragione ho partecipato a numerosi corsi di specializzazione in varie discipline, tra cui pilates, ginnastica posturale e kinesio taping. Senza naturalmente trascurare la preparazione rivolta all’assistenza medica di base e al primo soccorso. 

Nel 2015 mi sono diplomato “zone consultant” da Barry Sears, acquisendo quelle nozioni che mi permettono oggi di offrire una consulenza completa e qualificata non solo in ambito sportivo ma anche in quello alimentare. Credo infatti che una corretta alimentazione sia un elemento imprescindibile di ogni preparazione fisica di successo. 

Mettendo a frutto il mio interesse per i social network ho sviluppato un account Instagram (fil_the_situation) che ha gia’ raggiunto oltre 30.000 follower, in continuo aumento, nel quale fornisco gratuitamente consigli alimentari e di training. Rispondo inoltre personalmente alle e-mail di quanti mi domandino informazioni e suggerimenti per migliorare le loro metodologie di allenamento all’indirizzo filippo.scarpelli@libero.it. 

Sono esperto di allenamento funzionale, models workout e ho lavorato con numerose celebrità e personaggi famosi. Dal 2008 collaboro con Palestre Torino, società leader nel mondo del fitness torinese, e ricevo i miei clienti nella splendida location di Villa Glicini in viale Ceppi 5 a Torino.

name: Alina Astilean
bio:
Alina Astilean is an elite personal trainer & nutritionist located in Los Angeles, CA. Over the last 6 years, she has worked with countless clients focusing on weight loss, fat loss, and general health and wellness. Alina believes fitness and exercise should be made enjoyable so that it becomes an integral part of someones daily life, as opposed to a temporary plan or program. She works with every client to achieve real results that can be maintained over a lifetime, through customized meal plans and exercise programs that are simple to sustain. Her clients range from models, actors, and pro athletes, to lawyers, real estate brokers, and stay at home moms. 

Alina specializes in strength and conditioning programs and customizes all workouts to fit each person's specific schedule, areas of focus, and desired goals. Her unique training style allows clients to learn and understand how different exercise modalities affects their unique body type. Her extensive knowledge of nutrition also allows her to provide expert guidance to clients so they can best understand the types of foods and eating patterns that will allow them to get the most efficient results.

name: crossfitfoodie
bio:
Hi!  I’m Tara, an entrepreneur and a foodie, with a passion for all things food, fitness, wine, love, and travel. Follow me on my journey to live a life that’s full of adventure, excitement, and is nothing short of beautiful! 
I guess you could say I was born with a love of food rooted deep in my veins.  I remember as a little girl one of my favorite activities was helping my dad in the kitchen.  I’d roll up my sleeves, don an oversized apron that hung all the way to the floor, and immerse myself into the task at hand.  Fascinated, I’d watch my pops throw a little of this and a little of that into a pan, and viola, a delicious and delectable meal was made.    I adapted as the years went on to make sure that these delicious creations could fit into my fit lifestyle.  Today I continue the tradition of creativity and exploration through food, and wine.  But I don’t just stop there.  See, life is so much more than the meal on our plates.  I started cultivating a lifestyle centered on food and wine, and the people I enjoy those delicious feasts with, here, and all over the world. 
Over the years I’ve taken what started as a hobby and turned it into a passionate pursuit of a beautiful life.  You see, that’s my life motto: life is beautiful.  It really is, if you make it.  It started with food, and then I added in wine, and a soul thirsty for exploration and adventure.  I started traveling, relishing in the moments where I would sit in some new place, staring out into a beautiful setting, and savoring in the local fare. 
Along the way I met the most beautiful boy, James, with the prettiest eyes who has shown me more love and adventure than I ever imagined.  He’s changed my life.  And together with our little fluffy puppy we’ve dedicated ourselves to a life of passion & purpose.  We have a zest for adventure and we relish in the little moments that make our life so wonderful. 
And that brings me to you.  I started this blog as a way to share my love and passion for all things food & wine, health & fitness, travel, leadership, and lifestyle with you.  To me, these are all the things that make my life beautiful, and my hope is that by sharing this life with you, I can help you make your life a little brighter, a little bolder, and whole lot more beautiful.

name: WorldCalisthenicsOrganization
bio:
Founded by Kenneth Gallarzo and Brendan Cosso, the World Calisthenics Organization (WCO) was created for calisthenics enthusiasts by respected authorities on bodyweight training. The overarching intention of the WCO is to bring the calisthenics and street workout movement to the forefront of the mainstream fitness industry. 

The WCO achieves this by educating the community on safe and effective training methods and holding one-of-a-kind events. 

EDUCATION: 
StreetSport(r), the WCO strength and conditioning methodology, is an unique, practical and intuitive way to get stronger using only your bodyweight. Facilities worldwide are hosting StreetSport workshops and accrediting their staff in the WCO method. Many more are affiliating their teams and gym with the WCO for exclusive benefits and programs. FIND OUT MORE 

EVENTS: 
Battle of the Bars(r), a WCO original calisthenics tournament, has changed the game in the bodyweight community. The WCO was the first ever to hold a calisthenics competition on such a large and professional scale, with reach to nearly 37,000 onlookers at the LA Fit Expo January 2013. Combing elements of Street Workout, Parkour, Gymnastics, Free Running and Tricking, Battle of the Bars has become an intricate part of the growing community. WCO is the First to Market with the (1 on 1 ) Battle Style competition that includes the rounds system, weight categories, 10 point must system and an extremely intuitive scoring system

bio:
Hi, 
My name is Brice, model, TV character and actor. French mother tongue I currently speaks Italian & English. 
I parade and posed for the greatest designers in the world, Jean Paul Gaultier, John Galliano, Calvin Klein, Adidas, Reebok, Arena and i was noticed in an advertisement that has been around the world where he appears naked  

I made is cinema debut in 2012, as main character Faraz, an Iranian student in an Italian comedy “Universitari molto piu che amici “. In the same year i became a finalist of the french reality show Survivor on TF1. In 2015 I became a finalist of the italian reality show Survivor( VIP edition) on Canale5 “L’Isola dei Famosi” . 
I am twice married (August 28, 2010 and May 9, 2015) with Elena Falbo, Italian photographer, met in 2005 in Bora Bora (French Polynesia) with whom I live between France and Italy. 

“The world seems huge, but with a little bit of curiosity will we realize is so little. I like to consider myself as a globe trotter, a traveler but I do not like to see myself as a tourist. The world teaches us so much. I love watching, listening and especially back home with head full of memories and share my emotions and encounters. The tourist brings back only photos and fleeting encounters. Travelers always comes back more enriched by a different lifestyle, a different culture, a different language and therefore expanded its openness. One quickly realizes, that in life, we are far to understand everything… 
My biggest dream is and will always be, the one to visit and to know the entire world. Of course this will be not possible for me, even if i consider myself like a lucky guy, it is impossible to reach this goal cause different pattern as: time, economic reasons, etc. 
However, I reached forty countries, and despite this significant figure, I still can not be satisfied. Certainly I am very pleased to have had as much emotion, but traveling has become a drug for me. If a friend tells me about a place I never heard before, I immediately start looking at the offers on internet. No, this is not jealousy; if a friend tells me of an unknown place and this gave me chills, desire or even just curiosity, then the adventurer who sleeps in me wants to see, to know and discover. 
I like to share my adventures with those who wants to hear them, this is why I’ve decided to create this website / blog. I’d like to introduce you to these places and make you want to go or even simply feels the urge to know more about it. 

Living all these emotions is good but to live them with someone else is even better … 
thought my strongest memories are not relied only to beautiful locations in itself, but more then anything, attached to feelings shared with great people encountered throughout or traveling with. 

I am also a sports fan (especially of cross-fit). In the past, I have been a sport instructor for the tourism chain Club Med. Today I share my knowledge and passion with you; on social networks, I constantly respond to people who need some advice. I always take the time to answer to it, especially to those are in need. 

There’s have been a time in my life, where I founded myself in trouble with weight gain (at 105 kg I stopped weighing myself). 

I took hold of the situation and started training to earn physical fitness that today allows me to live by my image, working all around the world. 

A popular saying quotes “want is power” 

It all started when I got injured playing football, i broke my knee,no more sport for two years, needless to say that my dream of playing pro football was gone once and for all. At the same time have kept for two years the same way of eating (like a great athlete) but without burning a single calorie. I quickly found myself locked in a feeling of being ill. I became introverted and at school I often was the victim of unpleasant bullying. 

Watching a holiday tape from some vacations my mother asked me to comment it. I did not know what to say because I didn’t know who I was watching. Then I asked her who is this stranger on my holidays tape. She said if it was not me, it looked strangely like me … At that time, big awareness, I was able to finally put an image on my « disconfort». Then I decided to take me in hand. That day I even told my mother, with strong motivation, that one day I’d be on the covers of magazines … 

Nothing is impossible in life as long as there is motivation 

“to brave heart nothing impossible. “

bio:
Priscilla Rojas is a performance trainer and personal trainer certified through National Academy of Sports Medicine since 2013. She specializes in hybrid training by combining the elements of traditional resistance training and functional performance training. By combining these elements she supports her clients with achieving the aesthetic results that they're in search of, as well as their overall speed, strength and power. 
​ 
Priscilla's experience widely ranges from low-impact conditioning for beginner athletes to high intensity crossfit-like movements for conditioned athletes. All of her program designs are customized for the individual athlete and is progressive to ensure safety and athletic improvements. She offers programs for muscle build and fat burn, performance enhancement and a high intensity, outdoor-no equipment necessary program she calls Street Hiits. 
​ 
Described by many as sweet but tough, she is undoubtedly passionate about partnering with her clients through their tenacious journeys. She recognizes that at the end of the day, this quest should be a fun way of getting healthy and strong - "success is not a destination, but a journey".

name: Kardio Matters
bio:
We have a Mission 
KardioMatters.com is a very simple mission: to help other people reach their goals. We accomplish this by providing free information and advice on the best techniques as well as introduce everyone to the concept of the blood diet. There is the belief out there that people do not think that cardio exercises are important. However, it is one of the most important ways to avoid cardiovascular diseases, including heart disease and high blood pressure. The American Heart Association identifies cardio workouts to be one of the best ways to improve heart health. There are also people out there who believe that cardio workouts are going to hinder their gains. This has been proven incorrect time and time again. The people who believe this are likely the ones that are not doing the correct workouts for them or who are not doing the workouts properly and at the ideal target heart rate. KardioMatters.com is a simple website that focuses on helping people improving their weight and increasing muscle tone. Essentially, if you want to feel and look better, the information found on the website is going to have significant appeal. We will be talking about why cardio matters, what some of the top cardio workouts are, as well as information about the blood diet. We believe that the blood diet is one of the best ways to lose weight and maintain an ideal weight by focusing on foods that are best for your blood type. As time goes on, our mission will remain the same, though the content on our website will continue to grow – featuring a blog with ever-changing content as well as videos that provide details on some of the hottest and most effective cardio workouts. This is all free content that you will always have access to – and that can help you to achieve your goals and help to keep those around you motivated to reach their own personal goals. In support of our mission, we will be supporting the American Heart Association as well as Kids with Cancer. This is done through the sales of our apparel as some of the proceeds will be donated to the amazing organizations that focus on research and public education. Go ahead and bookmark KardioMatters.com now. We hope that you will continue to visit us and learn more about the importance of cardio workouts and how to get into the best shape of your life.

name: Studio One Islington
bio:
My sister and I wanted to start this studio as a lifestyle platform, helping not just to promote but also support a healthy lifestyle. Our dream is to make a healthy lifestyle accessible and convenient, whilst creating a friendly community feel. We both believe in social responsibility and therefore this ethos is central to our company. Not only do we have a charitable promise, but we encourage it in the partners we work with. 

Over the years we have been lucky enough to gain access to some amazing teachers, information, classes and healthy eating suppliers. They literally changed our lives and we hope they will in the least enrich yours. 

I am a city worker, new mum and personal trainer. Odd combination I know! I started in banking and quickly got sucked into a negative lifestyle of drinking, staying out late, eating badly and found my health went downhill. I was diagnosed with PCOS, had bad skin, no energy, no time for family and friends, felt very low and made bad decisions as they were made quickly and with a tired brain. I was not the person I wanted to be, or even liked. I started to take control of my life and self by getting a personal trainer about 8 years ago to help me get healthy and from there my interest in health and fitness grew, taking qualifications and now learning how food can heal the body. I tackled my PCOS firstly through drugs and now through diet and exercise managing my symptoms well. 

My sister Sarah has also undergone an amazing journey. From party girl with a terrible diet which left her overweight, she overnight decided to take control of her life. Starting with an easy to follow diet she started to learn more about nutrition and weight loss. This has inspired her to change her whole outlook on life, focusing on health and happiness trying new classes and recipes which in turn has led to weight loss and her sexier self both inside and out. 

We want Studio One to inspire you to be your best self, in what ever form that may be. We understand the daily stresses and struggles that everyone faces and we want to remove them if we can so you can have time to yourself and achieve your personal goals. 

We only have one life, share with us in our dream to be kind to ourselves and unleash our sexier side.

name: NaijaFitGoddessWorkouts
bio:
Hey there!  

My name is Honour and I'm in love with fitness and the joy it brings when people see their body changing. I love being a personal fitness coach and love working with people who are dedicated to making such a positive life change. 

I became a trainer after going through a very depressing moment in my life. I struggled with finding a passion and one day I realised how much better I always felt after going on a run or doing some kind of physical activity. Plus I've always been an athlete but because if depression i cut myself from all activities. One day I strolled upon a sign that said "become a personal trainer" (literally! ) and just like that I found my destiny. I ended up going to school for personal training and working with some of the top trainers in the industry. Some may feel I've chosen the wrong path but I always tell people that I didn't choose this path, this path chose me and I couldn't be happier. 

I was born in nigeria where lifting weights and having muscles (especially as a woman) is not "normal" but I'm looking to change that mindset. I plan on educating people here in the states and around the world (including my home country) on the importance of fitness/strength training and the benefits it brings. 

Whilst on this journey I'm also bettering myself in the fitness industry and my personal fitness level. I'm on the road to greatness and if you want to see how I'm working towards it you can follow me on my personal Instagram account @naijafitgoddess and on my Facebook page Honour also check me out on my YouTube page, you get to see what workouts I do to keep fit and incorporate it in your everyday life. 

"Greatness is in all of us you just have to believe it and act on it!" _honour olulu
